buffs_display.description: This ship can fire supermassive underwater torpedoes that inflict huge damage to Main Fleet ships they come in contact with.

buffs_display.description: This ship can fire supermassive underwater torpedoes that inflict huge damage to Main Fleet ships they come in contact with.

buffs_display.name: Repulsing Pyrotechnics
buffs_display.description:
When the battle starts, this ship can create 3 barriers that reduce the damage she takes. 
Every time your ships fire torpedoes, a main gun volley, or launch an airstrike, the barrier counter increases by 1, 2, and 2, respectively. Every time the barrier counter reaches {8|In game description icorrectly states 6.}, 1 barrier is negated.

buffs_display.name: Repulse's Resolve
buffs_display.description:
Each time a "Repulsing Pyrotechnics" barrier is negated, this ship's damage dealt increases and her attack pattern changes. 
Once all barriers have been negated, this ship will enter a ferocious attack phase.

buffs_display.name: Heart of Lava
buffs_display.description: This ship can launch huge lava projectiles, inflicting huge damage to Main Fleet ships they come in contact with as well as rendering aircraft carriers Detected.

buffs_display.name: Meteor Shower
buffs_display.description: This ship can launch a special barrage consisting of meteors.

buffs_display.name: Ashen Might - Storm
buffs_display.description:
This ship can execute a charged attack. Every time this attack goes off without being interrupted, this ship's damage dealt increases. 
The second time this attack is successfully executed, this ship's attack pattern changes and her ACC and damage dealt increases, but her damage taken increases.

buffs_display.name: Ashen Might - Lull
buffs_display.description:
Every time this ship's charged attack is interrupted as a result of damage from your ships, a portion of this ship's HP is restored and her damage taken is decreased. 
The second time this attack is interrupted, this ship's attack pattern changes and her damage taken decreases, but her ACC and damage dealt decreases.

buffs_display.name: Heart of Lava
buffs_display.description: This ship can launch huge lava projectiles, inflicting huge damage to Main Fleet ships they come in contact with as well as rendering aircraft carriers Detected.

buffs_display.name: Contagious Lament
buffs_display.description:
This ship summons a blue fog during battle. Ships inside this fog have reduced SPD and take more DMG.
The fog's debuffs become stronger the longer your ships remain inside the fog. The debuffs gradually disappear once your ships exit the fog.

buffs_display.name: Sea of Black Tears
buffs_display.description:
When an enemy ship's max HP falls below 50.0%, she begins recovering HP for the rest of the battle.
When an enemy ship's max HP falls below 20.0%, all her HP recovery will instead be dealt as DMG.

buffs_display.name: Dominion Expansion
buffs_display.description:
This ship exerts a field of dominion and summons Phantom Knights during battle. The Phantom Knights are resistant to attacks from non-META ships. 
Once all Phantom Knights have been defeated, this ship becomes weaker and permanently takes increased DMG.

buffs_display.name: META Affinity
buffs_display.description: This ship takes more DMG from your META ships, but also deals more DMG to your non-META ships.

buffs_display.name: Pillar of Sin
buffs_display.description:
When the battle starts: summons 4 [Pillars of Sin] that reduces DMG taken by Algrie META by {30.0%|In game incorrectly states 40.0%}.
When any [Pillar of Sin] takes DMG: {25.0%|The game incorrectly states only 20.0%.} of that DMG is instead redirected to Algrie META.

buffs_display.name: Expurgating Flame
buffs_display.description:
Algrie META's attacks inflict a special [Expurgating Flame] Burn status that deals high fixed DMG over a short duration.
Additionally, every 8s: inflicts [Expurgating Flame] on the target with the lowest HP percentage. This effect ignores the Main Fleet's Detection status.

buffs_display.name: Ironclad Ultimatum
buffs_display.description: 10s after the battle starts: decreases this ship's DMG taken by 20.0% until the battle ends.

buffs_display.name: Fragmented Alliance
buffs_display.description:
If you have ships from 2 or more different factions in your fleet: for each unique faction after the 1st, increases this ship's every stat by 5.0%. 
Collab ships, except for blueprint ships, are not counted.

buffs_display.name: Inevitable Fate
buffs_display.description: 50s after the battle starts: until the battle ends, increases this ship's DMG taken by 10.0% for every 4s passed.

buffs_display.name: Mechanized Support
buffs_display.description:
Kirov META summons 2 combat support units, Vspyshka and Kometa.
Vspyshka is a unit with Heavy Armor, close-range electric weapons, and homing bomb launchers, and takes increased torpedo DMG.Kometa is a unit with Medium Armor, long-range laser weapons, and bombs that cause freezing, and takes increased cannon DMG.
When a support unit is destroyed, it respawns after 3s.

buffs_display.name: Live and Die by Teamwork
buffs_display.description: Increases Kirov META's FP, TRP, and ACC for each active support unit {by 10%|Not mentioned by the game at all}. {Kirov META initially only takes 40% damage and for every support unit destroyed her damage taken increases by 10% (additively).|The game does not properly explain how this part of the skill works.}

buffs_display.name: Dimensional Transcendence
buffs_display.description: When your fleet fires a main gun salvo or launches an airstrike consecutively within 1.5 seconds of each other, Rodney META enters the Dimensional Transcendence state, increasing her SPD and making her untargetable and immune to DMG for 4s.

buffs_display.name: My Phantoms
buffs_display.description:
When the battle starts: summons 7 phantoms of Rodney. 
The phantoms do not attack and their DMG taken is set to 1. When a phantom is eliminated, Rodney META's DMG dealt increases and her DMG taken decreases. 
When the battle is at 10s remaining: all phantoms are eliminated.

buffs_display.name: Rodney's Demise
buffs_display.description: When all Rodney phantoms are eliminated, Rodney META enters the Dimensional Transcendence state; when this state ends, Rodney METAfires the final shot, ending the battle.

buffs_display.name: Tooth and Nail
buffs_display.description: Every time this ship loses 5.0% of her max HP in total, her DMG dealt increases by 5.0%.

buffs_display.name: Chains of Flickering Flames
buffs_display.description: When this ship hits one of your ships with her chain, that ship will be restrained, temporarily rendering her unable to attack or move and increases her DMG taken by 20.0%.

buffs_display.name: The Final Strike
buffs_display.description: When the battle is nearly over, this ship deploys the Council-Style MK XIII Orbital Cannon, dealing massive damage to all targets on the battlefield.

buffs_display.name: The Moon Waxes and Wanes
buffs_display.description:
The battlefield cycles between the Waxing Moon and Waning Moon states every 15s.
In the Waxing Moon state, Nagato META's DMG dealt increases by 20%, and the potency of your fleet's healing effects increases by 100%.
In the Waning Moon state, Nagato META's DMG dealt decreases by 20%, and the potency of your fleet's healing effects decreases by 50%.

buffs_display.name: The Flowers Bloom and Fall
buffs_display.description:
Creates a barrier around the battlefield which has different effects depending on if the Waxing Moon or Waning Moon state is active.
In the Waxing Moon state, all your ships inside the barrier take less DMG.
In the Waning Moon state, all your ships inside the barrier gradually lose HP.

buffs_display.name: Otherworldly Domain
buffs_display.description:
Upon losing 50% of her max HP in a single battle, Taihou META will deploy a special domain on the battlefield.
Within this domain, Taihou META and her summons deal 20.0% more DMG, and all healing effects from your ships are converted into damage.

If successfully charged: fires a special barrage; if this barrage hits even once: inflicts the Darkness ailment on your fleet for 10s; if the charge is interrupted: instead increases this ship's DMG dealt by 3.0% (can stack up to 20 times).

buffs_display.name: Surefire Shot
buffs_display.description: Every 20s: targets your Main Fleet ship that most recently launched an airstrike or fired her Main Guns and fires a special barrage at her (if no one in your Main Fleet has fired her Main Guns or launched an airstrike, this ship will target your whole Main Fleet). If the ship hit by this barrage has the Darkness ailment: additionally deals 10.0% of that shipgirl's HP in DMG.
